-- More Germans Are Still Working Beyond Age 50, FAZ Reports
-- B y   A l l i s o n   C o n n o l l y
-- 2012-01-05T19:33:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-05/more-germans-are-still-working-beyond-age-50-faz-reports.html
The number of Germans working past
the age of 50 is at its highest level since record-keeping began
in 2000,  Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung  reported in a preview of
an article to be published tomorrow, citing the federal
employment agency.  The number of Germans between ages 50 and 65 who worked as
of June 2011 increased 6.2 percent to 7.7 million from a year
earlier, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Allison Connolly in  Frankfurt  at 
 aconnolly4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Phil Serafino at   pserafino@bloomberg.net . 